The body of a newborn baby has been found in a plastic packet under a tree near a shopping mall in La Lucia, Umhlanga, north of Durban, paramedics said on Sunday. The gruesome discovery was made by an onsite security guard who alerted the Marshall Security emergency contact centre. Crisis Medical paramedics were dispatched to the scene and have confirmed the discovery to be the body of a newborn baby, Crisis Medical said in a statement. The scene had been secured and handed over to the South African Police Service for further investigation, the statement said. African News Agency (ANA)